{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J8Zk3azCnVjsxBHyX6FjGG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-6: Subagent Status Ownership + Time Budget Awareness\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer running harness-run,\n    10→I want the orchestrator to own all status writes and respect time budgets,\n    11→So that status is always correct and sessions don't fail at verification.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. Given a subagent completes dev-story with exit code 0 but doesn't update sprint-state.json, when the orchestrator checks after subagent return, then it updates the story status to the next phase (e.g., `in-review`) itself by calling `updateStoryStatus()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. Given a subagent fails (exit code non-zero), when the orchestrator checks after subagent return, then it sets the story status to `failed` and logs `Story {key} failed in {phase}` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. Given `shouldDeferPhase(phase, remainingMinutes)` is called with phase `verification` and 10 minutes remaining, when the estimate for verification is 20 minutes, then it returns `true` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. Given `shouldDeferPhase(phase, remainingMinutes)` is called with phase `dev-story` and 30 minutes remaining, when the estimate for dev-story is 15 minutes, then it returns `false` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. Given 10 minutes remaining and next phase is verification (~20min), when harness-run checks budget before the phase transition, then it defers with `[INFO] deferring verify to next session (Xmin remaining, 20min needed)` and saves current state <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. Given ralph prompt templates in `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` and verify prompt in `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`, when inspected after this story, then they contain zero instructions telling subagents to write sprint-state.json or sprint-status.yaml <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. Given `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` (new file) exists, when inspected, then it exports `shouldDeferPhase()` with phase time estimates: create-story=5min, dev-story=15min, code-review=10min, verification=20min, retro=5min <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. Given the session start time is tracked in the orchestrator, when `shouldDeferPhase()` is called, then remaining time is computed as `totalBudgetMinutes - elapsedMinutes` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→10. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→\n    26→## Technical Notes\n    27→\n    28→**Decision 11 (Process Enforcement).** Two gates: status ownership and time budget awareness.\n    29→\n    30→### Status Ownership\n    31→\n    32→Currently, subagents (dev, review, verify) are instructed to update sprint-status.yaml. This is unreliable -- reported 7+ times in retros. The fix: subagents are read-only on state. The orchestrator owns all status writes.\n    33→\n    34→Remove all instructions from ralph prompts and subagent prompts that tell them to update sprint-status.yaml or sprint-state.json.\n    35→\n    36→After each subagent completes, the orchestrator in `src/commands/run.ts`:\n    37→1. Reads the subagent's output/exit code\n    38→2. Determines the status transition (e.g., dev complete -> move to review)\n    39→3. Writes the status to sprint-state.json itself via `updateStoryStatus()`\n    40→4. Regenerates sprint-status.yaml (via story 11-2's derived view)\n    41→\n    42→```typescript\n    43→// After subagent returns\n    44→const exitCode = await waitForAgent(process);\n    45→if (exitCode === 0) {\n    46→  await updateStoryStatus(storyKey, nextPhaseStatus);\n    47→  output.ok(`Story ${storyKey} -> ${nextPhaseStatus}`);\n    48→} else {\n    49→  await updateStoryStatus(storyKey, 'failed');\n    50→  output.fail(`Story ${storyKey} failed in ${currentPhase}`);\n    51→}\n    52→```\n    53→\n    54→### Time Budget Awareness\n    55→\n    56→Phase time estimates (from architecture-v3.md):\n    57→- create-story: 5 min\n    58→- dev-story: 15 min\n    59→- code-review: 10 min\n    60→- verification: 20 min\n    61→- retro: 5 min\n    62→\n    63→Before each phase, check remaining time:\n    64→```typescript\n    65→function shouldDeferPhase(phase: string, remainingMinutes: number): boolean {\n    66→  const estimates: Record<string, number> = {\n    67→    'create-story': 5,\n    68→    'dev-story': 15,\n    69→    'code-review': 10,\n    70→    'verification': 20,\n    71→    'retro': 5,\n    72→  };\n    73→  return remainingMinutes < (estimates[phase] ?? 10);\n    74→}\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→Track session start time and total budget. Before each phase transition (Step 3b, 3c, 3d), call `shouldDeferPhase()`. If true, log `[INFO] deferring ${phase} to next session (${remaining}min remaining, ${estimate}min needed)` and save current state for next session.\n    78→\n    79→The session timeout is already tracked in ralph. Surface it to the TypeScript orchestrator.\n    80→\n    81→### Dependencies\n    82→\n    83→- `updateStoryStatus()` already exists in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` (from story 11-1)\n    84→- Sprint-status.yaml regeneration exists via `generateSprintStatusYaml()` (from story 11-2)\n    85→- `src/modules/sprint/timeout.ts` handles timeout capture but NOT phase budget estimation — the budget logic is new\n    86→\n    87→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    88→\n    89→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 7, 3, 4, 8): Create `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` with `shouldDeferPhase()` function and phase time estimate constants\n    90→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 7): Add unit tests for `shouldDeferPhase()` in `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/budget.test.ts`\n    91→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 2): Add post-subagent status ownership logic in `src/commands/run.ts` — after each subagent returns, call `updateStoryStatus()` based on exit code\n    92→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 5, 8): Add time budget check before each phase transition in `src/commands/run.ts` — call `shouldDeferPhase()` and defer if needed\n    93→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 6): Audit `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` and `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — remove any instructions telling subagents to write sprint-state.json or sprint-status.yaml\n    94→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify TypeScript compilation with `npm run build`\n    95→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 10): Run `npm test` and confirm zero regressions\n    96→\n    97→## Files to Change\n    98→\n    99→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Add status ownership after each subagent, add time budget checks before each phase transition\n   100→- `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` — NEW: `shouldDeferPhase()` function with phase time estimates, session budget tracking\n   101→- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/budget.test.ts` — NEW: Unit tests for budget logic\n   102→- `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — Remove all instructions telling subagents to write state files\n   103→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — Remove state-writing instructions from verify prompts\n   104→- `src/modules/sprint/index.ts` — Re-export budget functions\n   105→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"97e0b69d-7780-4d92-a428-95a4b19f3ed1","uuid":"a89519d9-35f5-4010-b8ca-50b27185a3a8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:34:53.922Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget.md","content":"# Story 14-6: Subagent Status Ownership + Time Budget Awareness\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer running harness-run,\nI want the orchestrator to own all status writes and respect time budgets,\nSo that status is always correct and sessions don't fail at verification.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Given a subagent completes dev-story with exit code 0 but doesn't update sprint-state.json, when the orchestrator checks after subagent return, then it updates the story status to the next phase (e.g., `in-review`) itself by calling `updateStoryStatus()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. Given a subagent fails (exit code non-zero), when the orchestrator checks after subagent return, then it sets the story status to `failed` and logs `Story {key} failed in {phase}` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. Given `shouldDeferPhase(phase, remainingMinutes)` is called with phase `verification` and 10 minutes remaining, when the estimate for verification is 20 minutes, then it returns `true` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. Given `shouldDeferPhase(phase, remainingMinutes)` is called with phase `dev-story` and 30 minutes remaining, when the estimate for dev-story is 15 minutes, then it returns `false` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. Given 10 minutes remaining and next phase is verification (~20min), when harness-run checks budget before the phase transition, then it defers with `[INFO] deferring verify to next session (Xmin remaining, 20min needed)` and saves current state <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n6. Given ralph prompt templates in `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` and verify prompt in `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`, when inspected after this story, then they contain zero instructions telling subagents to write sprint-state.json or sprint-status.yaml <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n7. Given `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` (new file) exists, when inspected, then it exports `shouldDeferPhase()` with phase time estimates: create-story=5min, dev-story=15min, code-review=10min, verification=20min, retro=5min <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n8. Given the session start time is tracked in the orchestrator, when `shouldDeferPhase()` is called, then remaining time is computed as `totalBudgetMinutes - elapsedMinutes` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n9. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n10. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n**Decision 11 (Process Enforcement).** Two gates: status ownership and time budget awareness.\n\n### Status Ownership\n\nCurrently, subagents (dev, review, verify) are instructed to update sprint-status.yaml. This is unreliable -- reported 7+ times in retros. The fix: subagents are read-only on state. The orchestrator owns all status writes.\n\nRemove all instructions from ralph prompts and subagent prompts that tell them to update sprint-status.yaml or sprint-state.json.\n\nAfter each subagent completes, the orchestrator in `src/commands/run.ts`:\n1. Reads the subagent's output/exit code\n2. Determines the status transition (e.g., dev complete -> move to review)\n3. Writes the status to sprint-state.json itself via `updateStoryStatus()`\n4. Regenerates sprint-status.yaml (via story 11-2's derived view)\n\n```typescript\n// After subagent returns\nconst exitCode = await waitForAgent(process);\nif (exitCode === 0) {\n  await updateStoryStatus(storyKey, nextPhaseStatus);\n  output.ok(`Story ${storyKey} -> ${nextPhaseStatus}`);\n} else {\n  await updateStoryStatus(storyKey, 'failed');\n  output.fail(`Story ${storyKey} failed in ${currentPhase}`);\n}\n```\n\n### Time Budget Awareness\n\nPhase time estimates (from architecture-v3.md):\n- create-story: 5 min\n- dev-story: 15 min\n- code-review: 10 min\n- verification: 20 min\n- retro: 5 min\n\nBefore each phase, check remaining time:\n```typescript\nfunction shouldDeferPhase(phase: string, remainingMinutes: number): boolean {\n  const estimates: Record<string, number> = {\n    'create-story': 5,\n    'dev-story': 15,\n    'code-review': 10,\n    'verification': 20,\n    'retro': 5,\n  };\n  return remainingMinutes < (estimates[phase] ?? 10);\n}\n```\n\nTrack session start time and total budget. Before each phase transition (Step 3b, 3c, 3d), call `shouldDeferPhase()`. If true, log `[INFO] deferring ${phase} to next session (${remaining}min remaining, ${estimate}min needed)` and save current state for next session.\n\nThe session timeout is already tracked in ralph. Surface it to the TypeScript orchestrator.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `updateStoryStatus()` already exists in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` (from story 11-1)\n- Sprint-status.yaml regeneration exists via `generateSprintStatusYaml()` (from story 11-2)\n- `src/modules/sprint/timeout.ts` handles timeout capture but NOT phase budget estimation — the budget logic is new\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1 (AC: 7, 3, 4, 8): Create `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` with `shouldDeferPhase()` function and phase time estimate constants\n- [x] Task 2 (AC: 7): Add unit tests for `shouldDeferPhase()` in `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/budget.test.ts`\n- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 2): Add post-subagent status ownership logic in `src/commands/run.ts` — after each subagent returns, call `updateStoryStatus()` based on exit code\n- [x] Task 4 (AC: 5, 8): Add time budget check before each phase transition in `src/commands/run.ts` — call `shouldDeferPhase()` and defer if needed\n- [x] Task 5 (AC: 6): Audit `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` and `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — remove any instructions telling subagents to write sprint-state.json or sprint-status.yaml\n- [x] Task 6 (AC: 9): Verify TypeScript compilation with `npm run build`\n- [x] Task 7 (AC: 10): Run `npm test` and confirm zero regressions\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `src/commands/run.ts` — Add status ownership after each subagent, add time budget checks before each phase transition\n- `src/modules/sprint/budget.ts` — NEW: `shouldDeferPhase()` function with phase time estimates, session budget tracking\n- `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/budget.test.ts` — NEW: Unit tests for budget logic\n- `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — Remove all instructions telling subagents to write state files\n- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — Remove state-writing instructions from verify prompts\n- `src/modules/sprint/index.ts` — Re-export budget functions\n","numLines":105,"startLine":1,"totalLines":105}}}
