owboat @anthropic-ai/claude-code` (showboat + claude CLI)\n    39→- Semgrep installed in common layer (`dockerfile-generator.ts:37`: `pipx install semgrep`)\n    40→\n    41→```\n    42→output: Test \"NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection includes Node.js 20\" passes\n    43→output: Test \"NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection includes showboat\" passes\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→## AC 4: Python project — Dockerfile includes Python 3, pip, venv, Semgrep\n    47→\n    48→**Verdict:** PASS\n    49→\n    50→**Evidence:** `src/lib/stacks/python.ts:242-249` — `PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection()` generates:\n    51→- `python3-pip python3-venv` (pip + venv)\n    52→- `pip install ... coverage pytest` (verification tooling)\n    53→- Semgrep in common layer\n    54→\n    55→```\n    56→output: Test \"PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection includes python3-pip\" passes\n    57→output: Test \"PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection includes python3-venv\" passes\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→## AC 5: Rust without Bevy — toolchain present, Bevy libs absent\n    61→\n    62→**Verdict:** PASS\n    63→\n    64→**Evidence:** `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts:211-221` — Bevy libs only added when `hasCargoDep(depsSection, 'bevy')` is true.\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→output: Test \"does NOT include Bevy system libs when bevy is not in Cargo.toml\" passes\n    68→output: Test \"includes Rust toolchain without Bevy\" passes\n    69→```\n    70→\n    71→## AC 6: StackProvider interface has getVerifyDockerfileSection, all providers implement, TypeScript compiles\n    72→\n    73→**Verdict:** PASS\n    74→\n    75→**Evidence:**\n    76→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts:98`: `getVerifyDockerfileSection(projectDir: string): string;`\n    77→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts:328`: implements method\n    78→- `src/lib/stacks/python.ts:242`: implements method\n    79→- `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts:200`: implements method\n    80→- `npm run build`: TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors\