{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FC9rnEXhvtoQ3qQ82LJoZE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n     2→\n     3→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — create-story (2026-03-25T05:55Z)\n     4→\n     5→**Problems encountered:**\n     6→- Original story quoted ~40 errors; actual count is 106. Epic definition was stale.\n     7→\n     8→**Risks identified:**\n     9→- AC2 (\"type annotation changes only\") boundary between type-only and logic change can be blurry\n    10→- 4 source files (not just test files) have errors, carrying higher risk\n    11→- 106 errors is large scope for single story\n    12→\n    13→**Observations:**\n    14→- All 5 ACs are cli-verifiable — fully automatable\n    15→- Error count has been growing for 13+ sessions\n    16→\n    17→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:13Z)\n    18→\n    19→**Problems encountered:**\n    20→- None — all 106 errors fixed across 20 files.\n    21→\n    22→**Borderline logic changes:**\n    23→- `dimensions.ts`: Changed `g.message` → `g.description`, removed nonexistent `g.fix`. Prior code was broken at runtime (undefined properties).\n    24→- `run.ts`: Changed `'in-review'` → `'review'` to match StoryStatus type. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'`.\n    25→- `docker-setup.ts`: `opensearch` property not in HarnessState interface but code writes it. Used `as HarnessState` cast.\n    26→\n    27→**Workarounds applied:**\n    28→- `deps.test.ts`/`otlp.test.ts`: Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks (vitest limitation with overloaded functions).\n    29→- `scan-cache.test.ts`: Removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` fields that never existed on `DetectedArtifacts`.\n    30→\n    31→**Observations:**\n    32→- 16 test files had type errors vs 4 source files — tests were the primary debt vector.\n    33→\n    34→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — code-review (2026-03-25T06:25Z)\n    35→\n    36→**Bugs found:**\n    37→- MEDIUM: `src/commands/run.ts` — `'in-review'` was invalid StoryStatus (should be `'review'`). Runtime behavior change, not type-only.\n    38→- MEDIUM: `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — `g.message` referenced non-existent property (correct: `g.description`). Produced `undefined` at runtime.\n    39→- MEDIUM: `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — `opensearch` not in HarnessState interface, suppressed with `as HarnessState` cast.\n    40→\n    41→**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n    42→- LOW: HarnessState missing `opensearch` field definition — tech debt for future story.\n    43→- LOW: Several test files use double-casts (`as unknown as T`) for partial mocks.\n    44→\n    45→**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n    46→\n    47→**Items sent back:** None. All fixes correct.\n    48→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"97e0b69d-7780-4d92-a428-95a4b19f3ed1","uuid":"f2ff0449-6fb8-4fee-af8a-081521e61fc8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:46:06.510Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — create-story (2026-03-25T05:55Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- Original story quoted ~40 errors; actual count is 106. Epic definition was stale.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC2 (\"type annotation changes only\") boundary between type-only and logic change can be blurry\n- 4 source files (not just test files) have errors, carrying higher risk\n- 106 errors is large scope for single story\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 5 ACs are cli-verifiable — fully automatable\n- Error count has been growing for 13+ sessions\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:13Z)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- None — all 106 errors fixed across 20 files.\n\n**Borderline logic changes:**\n- `dimensions.ts`: Changed `g.message` → `g.description`, removed nonexistent `g.fix`. Prior code was broken at runtime (undefined properties).\n- `run.ts`: Changed `'in-review'` → `'review'` to match StoryStatus type. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'`.\n- `docker-setup.ts`: `opensearch` property not in HarnessState interface but code writes it. Used `as HarnessState` cast.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- `deps.test.ts`/`otlp.test.ts`: Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks (vitest limitation with overloaded functions).\n- `scan-cache.test.ts`: Removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` fields that never existed on `DetectedArtifacts`.\n\n**Observations:**\n- 16 test files had type errors vs 4 source files — tests were the primary debt vector.\n\n### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — code-review (2026-03-25T06:25Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: `src/commands/run.ts` — `'in-review'` was invalid StoryStatus (should be `'review'`). Runtime behavior change, not type-only.\n- MEDIUM: `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — `g.message` referenced non-existent property (correct: `g.description`). Produced `undefined` at runtime.\n- MEDIUM: `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — `opensearch` not in HarnessState interface, suppressed with `as HarnessState` cast.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n- LOW: HarnessState missing `opensearch` field definition — tech debt for future story.\n- LOW: Several test files use double-casts (`as unknown as T`) for partial mocks.\n\n**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n\n**Items sent back:** None. All fixes correct.\n","numLines":48,"startLine":1,"totalLines":48}}}
