{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017EkKZmZm5EyjV3uQ1e51j9","type":"tool_result","content":"   907→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25 (Session 15)\n   908→\n   909→**Appended:** 2026-03-25T09:48Z\n   910→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 14-15 — Tech Debt Pipeline + Code Quality)\n   911→**Session:** 15\n   912→**Session window:** ~2026-03-25 02:05 UTC to ~2026-03-25 05:48 UTC (~4 hours)\n   913→**Ralph runs:** 2 (first run: iterations 1-13, ~4h40m; second run: iteration 1+, ~15m before this retro)\n   914→\n   915→---\n   916→\n   917→## 1. Session Summary\n   918→\n   919→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Commit Time (UTC+4) | Notes |\n   920→|-------|------|---------|---------------------|-------|\n   921→| 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection | Epic 14 | done | 02:40 | Clean pass |\n   922→| 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup | Epic 14 | done | 02:58 | 1 retry |\n   923→| 14-7-fix-beads-flags-ralph-tracking-proof-docs | Epic 14 | done | 04:44 | Clean pass |\n   924→| 15-1-ci-file-size-gate | Epic 15 | done | 04:58 | Clean pass |\n   925→| 15-2-eslint-no-empty-catch-boundary-tests | Epic 15 | done | 05:41 | Clean pass |\n   926→| 15-3-template-migration-static-files | Epic 15 | done | 09:45 | 1 retry, completed in 2nd ralph run |\n   927→| 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors | Epic 15 | review | — | Story created + dev done, not yet committed |\n   928→| 14-4-observability-backend-choice | Epic 14 | stuck | — | Exceeded retry limit (10+), flagged |\n   929→| 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile | Epic 14 | stuck | — | 8+ retries across session, never completed |\n   930→| 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget | Epic 14 | stuck | — | Still in verifying, no progress |\n   931→\n   932→**Net progress:** 6 stories completed (done). 1 in review. 3 stuck in verifying. Overall sprint: 61 of 66 stories done (92%). 5 remaining.\n   933→\n   934→---\n   935→\n   936→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   937→\n   938→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n   939→\n   940→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   941→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   942→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `dimensions.ts` used `g.message` and `g.fix` — nonexistent properties on the actual object. Runtime bug (undefined values). Changed to `g.description`, removed `g.fix`. | Yes |\n   943→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `run.ts` used `'in-review'` string literal but `StoryStatus` type only has `'review'`. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'` — cross-system inconsistency. | Partially — TS fixed, bash/yaml not audited |\n   944→| LOW | 15-4 | `docker-setup.ts` writes `opensearch` property not in `HarnessState` interface. Used `as HarnessState` cast to suppress. | Workaround only |\n   945→\n   946→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   947→\n   948→| Story | Workaround | Debt Level |\n   949→|-------|-----------|------------|\n   950→| 15-4 | `deps.test.ts`/`otlp.test.ts`: Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks (vitest limitation) | Low — cosmetic |\n   951→| 15-4 | `scan-cache.test.ts`: Removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` fields — never existed on `DetectedArtifacts`. Tests were asserting phantom properties. | Low — test cleanup, not debt |\n   952→| 15-4 | `docker-setup.ts`: `as HarnessState` cast to bypass missing `opensearch` on interface | Medium — interface needs expanding |\n   953→\n   954→### Verification Gaps\n   955→\n   956→| Story | Gap |\n   957→|-------|-----|\n   958→| 14-4-observability-backend-choice | Has been in \"verifying\" for 10+ retries across 2 ralph runs. Either the verification criteria are impossible to satisfy without Docker/infrastructure, or the subagent is looping without progress. |\n   959→| 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile | Same pattern — 8+ retries. Likely Docker-dependent verification that cannot pass in the current sandbox. |\n   960→| 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget | Stuck in verifying with no retry log entries. May not have been attempted this session. |\n   961→\n   962→### Scope Estimation Error\n   963→\n   964→| Story | Issue |\n   965→|-------|-------|\n   966→| 15-4 | Epic definition quoted ~40 TS errors. Actual count: 106 across 20 files. 2.65x underestimate. Epic definition was stale by 13+ sessions. |\n   967→\n   968→### Tooling/Infrastructure\n   969→\n   970→- Ralph's first run burned 13 iterations over ~4h40m but only landed 4 stories (14-7, 15-1, 15-2). The other 9 iterations were wasted retrying 14-4 and 14-5.\n   971→- Retry limit for 14-4 was 10, meaning 10 full subagent invocations (~15 min each) were consumed with zero output. That is ~2.5 hours of compute wasted on a single stuck story.\n   972→\n   973→---\n   974→\n   975→## 3. What Went Well\n   976→\n   977→- **Six stories completed and committed.** Strong throughput for non-blocked work.\n   978→- **15-4 dev was clean.** 106 TS errors fixed across 20 files with no regressions — session issues log reports zero implementation problems.\n   979→- **Test files were the debt vector, not source files.** 16 of 20 files with errors were tests. The core source code is in better shape than the error count suggested.\n   980→- **Story pipeline end-to-end** (create-story -> dev-story -> code-review -> verification -> commit) continues to work reliably for stories that don't depend on Docker infrastructure.\n   981→- **Sprint at 92% completion** (61/66 done).\n   982→\n   983→---\n   984→\n   985→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   986→\n   987→- **~2.5 hours wasted on retry loops for 14-4.** Ralph retried a stuck story 10 times before flagging it, burning significant compute. The story has been stuck across multiple sessions now.\n   988→- **14-5 same pattern.** 8+ retries with no progress. Combined with 14-4, roughly 3 hours of the 4h40m first run was wasted.\n   989→- **Three stories stuck in \"verifying\" with no clear resolution path.** 14-4, 14-5, 14-6 have been in this state since at least session 14. They are likely Docker-dependent and will never pass without infrastructure changes.\n   990→- **Stale epic scope data.** 15-4 was scoped at ~40 errors but had 106. If this had caused a story failure or split, it would have wasted a full iteration. Fortunately dev handled it in one pass.\n   991→- **`'in-review'` vs `'review'` inconsistency** — this is a cross-system bug. The TypeScript type says `'review'` but bash/yaml tooling may still emit `'in-review'`. This was fixed locally in run.ts but the broader system is unaudited.\n   992→\n   993→---\n   994→\n   995→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   996→\n   997→### Patterns to Repeat\n   998→\n   999→- **Skip-and-continue for stuck stories works.** Session 14's retro recommended this, and the second ralph run (after retry counter reset) immediately landed 15-3. Fast failure is better than long retry loops.\n  1000→- **TS compilation error fixes are safe bulk operations.** 106 errors across 20 files in one story with zero regressions. Good candidate for batch work.\n  1001→\n  1002→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1003→\n  1004→- **10 retries before flagging is too many for verification-stuck stories.** If a story fails verification 3 times in a row, it should be flagged, not retried 7 more times. The current max_story_retries=10 is too generous for verifying-stage failures.\n  1005→- **Do not trust epic-level error counts.** Always re-audit at story creation time. The 13-session-stale count was misleading.\n  1006→- **\"Verifying\" is a black hole.** Stories that enter verifying and fail get retried indefinitely. There is no mechanism to distinguish \"needs one more try\" from \"fundamentally blocked.\"\n  1007→\n  1008→---\n  1009→\n  1010→## 6. Action Items\n  1011→\n  1012→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1013→\n  1014→| # | Action | Owner | Context |\n  1015→|---|--------|-------|---------|\n  1016→| 1 | **Resolve 14-4, 14-5, 14-6.** Either mark them as blocked with a reason, manually verify and close, or descope from this sprint. They have been stuck for 2+ sessions and waste retry budget every run. | Human | 3 stories, all in \"verifying\" |\n  1017→| 2 | **Audit `'in-review'` vs `'review'` across bash/yaml tooling.** 15-4 fixed the TS side but the string mismatch may exist in ralph scripts, sprint-status.yaml generation, or other shell-based tools. | Next session | Cross-system consistency |\n  1018→\n  1019→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1020→\n  1021→| # | Action | Owner | Context |\n  1022→|---|--------|-------|---------|\n  1023→| 3 | **Reduce max_story_retries for verification failures to 3.** Dev failures can retry more (code changes each time). Verification failures on the same code are usually infrastructure-blocked. Differentiate retry budgets by phase. | Dev | ralph config |\n  1024→| 4 | **Add `opensearch` to `HarnessState` interface.** The `as HarnessState` cast in docker-setup.ts is hiding a real interface gap. | Dev | 15-4 workaround |\n  1025→| 5 | **Refresh epic error counts at sprint planning time.** Add a pre-sprint audit step that re-runs `tsc --noEmit` (or equivalent) to get current counts before story scoping. | Process | Stale scope data |\n  1026→\n  1027→### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n  1028→\n  1029→| # | Action | Context |\n  1030→|---|--------|---------|\n  1031→| 6 | Vitest overloaded-function mock typing workaround — monitor for upstream fix | 15-4 test workaround |\n  1032→| 7 | `scan-cache.test.ts` was asserting phantom properties (`hasBmalph`, `bmalpthFiles`) — audit other test files for similar ghost assertions | Test quality |\n  1033→| 8 | Ralph retry-waste metric — track \"iterations spent on stuck stories\" per session to quantify compute waste | Observability |\n  1034→\n  1035→---\n  1036→\n  1037→### Session Velocity (Updated)\n  1038→\n  1039→| Session | Stories Attempted | Stories Completed (done) | Stories Stuck |\n  1040→|---------|-------------------|--------------------------|---------------|\n  1041→| 10 | 4 | 4 | 0 |\n  1042→| 11 | 9 | 6 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1043→| 12 | 1 | 0 | 1 (ENOSPC) |\n  1044→| 13 | 3 | 0 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1045→| 14 | 1 | 1 | 0 (3 skipped) |\n  1046→| **15** | **10** | **6** | **3 (verifying)** |\n  1047→\n  1048→Session 15 had the highest attempt count and completion count in recent sessions. However, the 3 stuck stories are the same 3 from session 14 — they have not moved. The \"verifying\" bottleneck from sessions 11-14 persists. Until 14-4, 14-5, and 14-6 are resolved or descoped, they will continue consuming retry budget every session.\n  1049→\n  1050→---\n  1051→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0149VquQtU7Sj7JQpT7y6K7c","session_id":"97e0b69d-7780-4d92-a428-95a4b19f3ed1","uuid":"b4e0b457-b2a5-4f8a-aee9-1dfb296d18d6","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:47:11.597Z"}
