{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DMYAvd6EVBH9ToSBqvnVuJ","type":"tool_result","content":"  1052→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25 (Session 16 / End-of-Day Update)\n  1053→\n  1054→**Appended:** 2026-03-25T10:30Z\n  1055→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 14-15 — Tech Debt Pipeline + Code Quality)\n  1056→**Session:** 16 (continuation from session 15)\n  1057→**Session window:** ~2026-03-25 06:00 UTC to ~2026-03-25 06:30 UTC (~30 minutes)\n  1058→\n  1059→---\n  1060→\n  1061→## 1. Session Summary\n  1062→\n  1063→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Commit Time (UTC+4) | Notes |\n  1064→|-------|------|---------|---------------------|-------|\n  1065→| 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors | Epic 15 | done | 10:30 | Was \"in review\" at session 15 retro; now committed |\n  1066→\n  1067→**Net progress:** 1 story moved from review to done. Sprint: 62 of 66 stories done (94%). 4 remaining (14-4, 14-5, 14-6 stuck in verifying; 15-5 in backlog).\n  1068→\n  1069→---\n  1070→\n  1071→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1072→\n  1073→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n  1074→\n  1075→All issues for 15-4 were already documented in the session 15 retro. No new issues surfaced during the verification-to-commit phase. To recap the key findings from the session issues log:\n  1076→\n  1077→| Severity | Story | Issue | Status |\n  1078→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n  1079→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `dimensions.ts`: `g.message`/`g.fix` referenced nonexistent properties — runtime bug producing `undefined` | Fixed (changed to `g.description`, removed `g.fix`) |\n  1080→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `run.ts`: `'in-review'` not in `StoryStatus` type — cross-system string mismatch | Fixed in TS; bash/yaml unaudited |\n  1081→| MEDIUM | 15-4 | `docker-setup.ts`: `opensearch` not in `HarnessState` — suppressed with cast | Workaround only |\n  1082→\n  1083→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n  1084→\n  1085→| Story | Workaround | Debt Level |\n  1086→|-------|-----------|------------|\n  1087→| 15-4 | `as HarnessState` cast in docker-setup.ts | Medium — interface needs `opensearch` field |\n  1088→| 15-4 | Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks in deps.test.ts/otlp.test.ts | Low — vitest limitation |\n  1089→\n  1090→### Verification Gaps\n  1091→\n  1092→No new gaps. The 3 stuck stories (14-4, 14-5, 14-6) remain unchanged from session 15.\n  1093→\n  1094→### Scope Estimation\n  1095→\n  1096→Story 15-4 scoped at ~40 TS errors; actual count was 106 across 20 files (2.65x underestimate). Despite this, dev completed in a single pass with no regressions. Code review found all changes correct.\n  1097→\n  1098→---\n  1099→\n  1100→## 3. What Went Well\n  1101→\n  1102→- **15-4 completed cleanly.** 106 TS compilation errors fixed across 20 files. Zero regressions. Code review passed with no items sent back.\n  1103→- **Test coverage at 97.1%**, all 156 files above 80% floor.\n  1104→- **Sprint at 94% completion** (62/66 done). Highest completion rate in the project's history.\n  1105→- **Session issues log was thorough.** Every subagent (create-story, dev-story, code-review) contributed meaningful observations. The borderline logic changes in dimensions.ts and run.ts were correctly flagged.\n  1106→- **7 stories completed across today's sessions** (14-2, 14-3, 14-7, 15-1, 15-2, 15-3, 15-4). Strong daily throughput.\n  1107→\n  1108→---\n  1109→\n  1110→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1111→\n  1112→- **3 stories remain stuck in \"verifying\" with no resolution.** 14-4, 14-5, and 14-6 have been stuck for 3+ sessions now. They consumed ~3 hours of compute in session 15's first ralph run with zero output. This is the single largest waste of the sprint.\n  1113→- **Cross-system `'in-review'` vs `'review'` inconsistency remains unaudited.** The TS type was fixed but bash/yaml tooling was not checked. This could cause silent failures in ralph's story status tracking.\n  1114→- **HarnessState interface is incomplete.** The `opensearch` property exists in runtime code but not in the type definition. The cast workaround hides real type safety.\n  1115→\n  1116→---\n  1117→\n  1118→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1119→\n  1120→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1121→\n  1122→- **Bulk TS error fixing works well as a single story.** Even at 106 errors, the work was mechanical and low-risk. Future type-debt cleanup can follow this pattern.\n  1123→- **Session issues log as retrospective input** — the create-story/dev/review pipeline producing structured issue reports made this retro straightforward. Every problem was already documented with severity and fix status.\n  1124→\n  1125→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1126→\n  1127→- **Do not let stories sit in \"verifying\" across sessions without human intervention.** 14-4/14-5/14-6 have now consumed 3+ sessions of retry budget. The automated pipeline cannot resolve infrastructure-blocked stories.\n  1128→- **Do not trust stale counts from epic definitions.** Always re-audit at story creation time.\n  1129→\n  1130→---\n  1131→\n  1132→## 6. Action Items\n  1133→\n  1134→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1135→\n  1136→| # | Action | Context |\n  1137→|---|--------|---------|\n  1138→| 1 | **Resolve 14-4, 14-5, 14-6** — manually verify and close, mark as blocked, or descope. They have been stuck 3+ sessions. | 3 stories in \"verifying\" consuming retry budget |\n  1139→| 2 | **Audit `'in-review'` vs `'review'` in bash/yaml** — check ralph scripts, sprint-status.yaml generation, and any shell tooling that emits story status strings. | Cross-system string mismatch from 15-4 |\n  1140→\n  1141→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1142→\n  1143→| # | Action | Context |\n  1144→|---|--------|---------|\n  1145→| 3 | **Add `opensearch` to `HarnessState` interface** | docker-setup.ts cast workaround |\n  1146→| 4 | **Reduce max_story_retries for verification-phase failures to 3** | Session 15 burned 10 retries on 14-4 |\n  1147→| 5 | **Add pre-sprint audit step** — run `tsc --noEmit` to get current error counts before story scoping | Stale epic data caused 2.65x underestimate |\n  1148→\n  1149→### Backlog (Track but Not Urgent)\n  1150→\n  1151→| # | Action | Context |\n  1152→|---|--------|---------|\n  1153→| 6 | Vitest overloaded-function mock typing — monitor for upstream fix | Low-impact test workaround |\n  1154→| 7 | Audit test files for phantom property assertions (like `hasBmalph`) | scan-cache.test.ts had ghost fields |\n  1155→| 8 | Ralph retry-waste metric — track iterations spent on stuck stories per session | Compute waste observability |\n  1156→\n  1157→---\n  1158→\n  1159→### End-of-Day Sprint Summary (2026-03-25)\n  1160→\n  1161→**Total stories completed today:** 7 (14-2, 14-3, 14-7, 15-1, 15-2, 15-3, 15-4)\n  1162→**Sprint completion:** 62/66 (94%)\n  1163→**Remaining:** 14-4 (verifying), 14-5 (verifying), 14-6 (verifying), 15-5 (backlog)\n  1164→**Sessions today:** 7 (sessions 10-16)\n  1165→**Estimated compute hours today:** ~12 hours across all ralph runs\n  1166→\n  1167→### Session Velocity (Updated)\n  1168→\n  1169→| Session | Stories Attempted | Stories Completed (done) | Stories Stuck |\n  1170→|---------|-------------------|--------------------------|---------------|\n  1171→| 10 | 4 | 4 | 0 |\n  1172→| 11 | 9 | 6 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1173→| 12 | 1 | 0 | 1 (ENOSPC) |\n  1174→| 13 | 3 | 0 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1175→| 14 | 1 | 1 | 0 (3 skipped) |\n  1176→| 15 | 10 | 6 | 3 (verifying) |\n  1177→| **16** | **1** | **1** | **0** |\n  1178→\n  1179→The 3 stuck stories (14-4, 14-5, 14-6) were not attempted in session 16. Until they are manually resolved or descoped, they should be excluded from ralph's story selection to stop wasting retry budget."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0149VquQtU7Sj7JQpT7y6K7c","session_id":"97e0b69d-7780-4d92-a428-95a4b19f3ed1","uuid":"76d470a0-ec87-4dda-9c9d-ee6b8b59cd21","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:47:17.493Z"}
